					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79054379" rend="visible">
						<summary>The second volume of the Bible with masorah magna and parva.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n79054379">
							<locus from="1r" to="302v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Tana"kh</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">תנ"ך</title>
							<decoNote type="initial">Initial-word panels with penwork decoration, in colours, gold and silver.<locus n="1r, 31r, 70r, 103r, 107v, 109r, 112v, 113r, 114r, 116v, 117v, 118v, 120r, 121r, 126v, 130r, 174r, 186r, 195v, 202r, 208r, 222r, 241v, 258v, 260v, 263r, 268r, 270v, 276r, 286v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="initial">Numerous initial-word panels decorated with pen-flourishing, in red and blue ink.</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="initial">
								<locus n="174r"/>Illuminated headings in addition to the opening illumination.</decoNote>
							<note>
								<p>Second of the two uniform volumes of the Hebrew Bible, the other being Harley 5710, see <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">54</ref>; consists of Lesser Prophets and Hagiographa. </p>
								<p>Since the style of the illumination points to the end of the 13th century as date of production, the date in the purchase note on 302v is probably erroneous, and instead of <date calendar="Hebrew">5000</date>, that is, <date calendar="Gregorian">1240</date>, it should be <date calendar="Hebrew">5100</date>, that is, <date calendar="Gregorian">1340</date>. </p>
								<p>See <ref target="Tahan_2007" type="page">31</ref>, <ref target="Wright_1966" type="page">227</ref>, <ref target="Wright_1972" type="page">254, 461</ref>, <ref target="Metzger_1982" type="page">304</ref>, <ref target="Narkiss_1984" type="page">57</ref>, <ref target="Ebenbauer_1991" type="page">131-150</ref>, <ref target="BL_2007" type="page">149</ref>. </p>
							</note>
